cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing techniques such as sentence compression and summarization. It may also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the paper focuses on query-focused multi-document summarization. Additionally, the use of learning-based compression models and beam search decoder suggests that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the integration of various metrics into the compression process may suggest that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
